The paper deals with the classic online bin packing problem, which is a well-studied problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also introduces new methods and approaches to the problem, which involve partitioning items into classes based on sizes and packing them into multiple types of bins, which can be seen as a game-theoretic approach (cs.GT). The paper also simplifies the analysis of the algorithms, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper provides a new algorithm with a better competitive ratio, which can be seen as a computational complexity problem (cs.CC).
